    <briefdescription>
<para>UQ15 (offset-binary uint16) to float converter. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Decodes an offset-binary uint16 (UQ15) sample back to a normalised float:</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">x̂<sp/>=<sp/>((int32_t)u<sp/>-<sp/>32768)<sp/>*<sp/>(1<sp/>/<sp/>scale)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>This is the exact inverse of F32ToUQ15 with the same scale.</para>
<para>The inverse scale is pre-computed at construction time so the step path is a single subtract and multiply.</para>
<para>Lifecycle: create -&gt; (step / steps / reset)* -&gt; destroy</para>
<para>Example: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structuq15__to__f32__state__t" kindref="compound">uq15_to_f32_state_t</ref><sp/>*obj<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="uq15__to__f32__core_8h_1abe95b057d65012e2dc26abf3ab8bc041" kindref="member">uq15_to_f32_create</ref>(32768.0f);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">float</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>y<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="uq15__to__f32__core_8h_1a80933679a5d0013e329aa73b486f4e76" kindref="member">uq15_to_f32_step</ref>(obj,<sp/>32768U);<sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>y<sp/>==<sp/>0.0f<sp/><sp/>(mid-scale)</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">float</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>z<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="uq15__to__f32__core_8h_1a80933679a5d0013e329aa73b486f4e76" kindref="member">uq15_to_f32_step</ref>(obj,<sp/>0U);<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>z<sp/>==<sp/>-1.0f<sp/>(negative<sp/>FS)</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="uq15__to__f32__core_8h_1a83e1ba7ed4899235f322b3cf753768eb" kindref="member">uq15_to_f32_destroy</ref>(obj);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
